a","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":25,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705210,"age":38,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Hannah Chute was born in 1562, in Leicestershire, England, her father, David Chute, was 22 and her mother, Judith Ruth Searl, was 22. She married Thomas Paybody about 1580, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1607, in England, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1562–1607":"1562–1607","1563–1610":"1563–1610","1581–1661":"1581–1661","1584–Male":"1584–Surnud","1540–1595":"1540–1595","1540–Female":"1540–Surnud","about 1580":"umbes 1580","1571":"1571","1581":"1581","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","1610":"1610","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","1562":"1562","1584":"1584","1595":"1595","1540":"1540","1661":"1661","1607":"1607","Leicestershire, England":"Leic